What is the command for listing files in Linux?
ls . You would use ls command which stands for list. 

What is the command for listing files in Linux in reverse time order?
ls -r . The ls will list the files and -r will do it in reverse.

What is the command for listing files in Linux in reverse time order with 
access times and permissions?
ls -lrt . The ls will list the files and -lrt will show the list with access
times and permissions in reverse time order. 

Why would you do this?
You would use this to see the access times and permissions of a drive or file.
